# Accessibility

See also: **`interaction-polish.mdc`** (keyboard parity, focus, feedback), **`shadcn-ui-usage.mdc`**, **`design-tokens.mdc`** (contrast via semantic colors, not hard-coded values).

Polish without accessibility is incomplete. AI-generated UIs often look fine but fail keyboard, screen reader, and focus management.

## Baseline

- Use **semantic HTML** first (`button`, `nav`, `main`, `label`, `h1`тАУ`h6`).
- Prefer **shadcn/Radix primitives** тАФ they ship focus traps and roles for Dialog, Sheet, Dropdown, etc. Do not rebuild modals with `div` + `onClick`.
- Every interactive control must be **keyboard operable** (Tab, Enter/Space, Escape where expected).
- **Visible focus** тАФ never `outline: none` without an equivalent focus ring (`interaction-polish.mdc`). Use `ring-ring` / focus tokens тАФ not hard-coded focus colors (`design-tokens.mdc`).

## Keyboard navigation

| Pattern              | Requirement                                              |
| -------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------- |
| Buttons / links      | Focusable; Enter activates                               |
| Menus / dropdowns    | Arrow keys; Escape closes; focus returns to trigger      |
| Dialogs / sheets     | Focus trap while open; Escape closes; restore focus      |
| Tabs                 | Arrow keys between tabs when using Radix Tabs            |
| Tables with actions  | Row actions reachable without mouse-only hover-only UI   |

**Do not** rely on `onMouseEnter` as the only way to reach controls.

## Dialogs & focus trap

```tsx
// Good тАФ shadcn Dialog handles focus trap, aria-modal, Escape
<Dialog open={open} onOpenChange={setOpen}>
  <DialogContent>
    <DialogTitle>Edit profile</DialogTitle>
    ...
  </DialogContent>
</Dialog>
```

- Every dialog needs a **`DialogTitle`** (visible or `className="sr-only"`).
- Use **`DialogDescription`** when context helps screen readers.
- On close, focus should return to the trigger тАФ Radix does this when used correctly; do not steal focus manually unless required.

## Labels & names

```tsx
// Bad тАФ icon-only button
<Button size="icon" onClick={onDelete}><TrashIcon /></Button>

// Good
<Button size="icon" onClick={onDelete} aria-label="Delete campaign">
  <TrashIcon aria-hidden="true" />
</Button>
```

- Associate **`<Label htmlFor={id}>`** with inputs; or `aria-label` / `aria-labelledby` when label is visually hidden.
- **Do not** use `placeholder` as the only label.

## Dynamic content announcements

| Event            | Pattern                                                    |
| ---------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------- |
| Loading (region) | `aria-busy="true"` on the loading container when appropriate |
| Async success    | `aria-live="polite"` region for toasts (Sonner handles many cases) |
| Form errors      | Link errors with `aria-describedby`; announce summary for screen readers |
| Route change     | Move focus to `h1` or use `aria-live` for main content title |

For **inline validation**, set `aria-invalid` on the field and connect the error id:

```tsx
<Input id="email" aria-invalid={!!errors.email} aria-describedby={errors.email ? "email-error" : undefined} />
{errors.email && <p id="email-error" role="alert">{errors.email.message}</p>}
```

## Loading & skeletons

- Skeleton regions should not trap focus.
- When content replaces a skeleton, avoid **focus loss** on the control the user was using.
- Prefer **page-level** `h1` that describes the view тАФ not only `div` + `text-lg font-bold` without heading role.

## Color & motion

- **Do not** convey state by color alone (add text, icon, or pattern).
- Respect **`prefers-reduced-motion`** for non-essential animation (`interaction-polish.mdc`).

## Images & icons

- Meaningful images: **`alt`** text.
- Decorative images: `alt=""` or `aria-hidden` on icons with text label nearby.

## Tables

- Use `<table>`, `<thead>`, `<th scope="col">` for data tables.
- Sort buttons need accessible names (`aria-label="Sort by date"`).

## Testing checklist (manual)

- [ ] Tab through the flow without a mouse; no keyboard traps except intentional modals.
- [ ] Escape closes overlays; focus returns sensibly.
- [ ] Icon-only controls have accessible names.
- [ ] Form errors are perceivable without color alone.
- [ ] Dialogs have titles and readable structure.

## Checklist for PRs

- [ ] New interactive UI uses shadcn primitives or correct roles/labels.
- [ ] Modals/sheets use Dialog/Sheet тАФ not custom div overlays.
- [ ] Async errors and critical success states are announced or visible in text.
- [ ] No mouse-only critical paths.
